7.Given a number n, determine whether it is a prime number or not.
Note: A prime number is a number greater than 1 that has no positive divisors other than 1 and itself.
platform : Geeks For Geeks
SOURCE CODE :      class Solution {
                  static boolean isPrime(int n) {
                 int count=0;
                   for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
                    if(n%i==0){
                     count++; }   }
                  if(count==2){
                     return true;
                 } return false; } }
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/prime-number2314/1
8.You are given an array of integers arr[]. You have to reverse the given array.
platform : Geeks For Geeks
SOURCE CODE :    class Solution {
                 public void reverseArray(int arr[]) {
                 int start=0;
                 int end=arr.length-1;
                 while(start<end){
                  int temp=arr[start];
                    arr[start]=arr[end];
                      arr[end]=temp;
                         start++;
                          end--;  } }}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/reverse-an-array/1
